metadata.description: This is a song about not looking back in the midst of chaos. Life flies by so quickly we can take a minute to look away or we'll miss even more.

lyrics.text:
If I look away
These days would fly past me
Let's sit around wasting time
On the bad things
I'm cutting my place in line
And i'm not asking
It's enough we said all this time
And it's not lasting

Can't give it one more go
I'm going on blasting
Boxed up, put away
You're with the past things
I'm stuck in my head
Can't get it past me
Best luck to you
I'll leave you in the last scene
I'm scared to just let you go
I would keep you close
And you felt like home
One I could call at least
I just hit a brand new low
Only up I'll go
Nothing else im supposed to
About to fall with ease

It's too late
Know the price paid
It's too late
Said now I'm never coming back
It's too late
Price paid
Price paid
Price paid
If I look away
These days would fly past me
Lets sit around wasting time
On the bad things
